==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheal
<hw>Wheal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>whele</ets>,
AS. <ets>hwele</ets> putrefaction, <ets>hwelian</ets> to putrefy.]</ety>
<def>A pustule; a whelk.</def> <rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wheal
<hw>Wheal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Wale</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A more or less elongated mark raised by a stroke;
also, a similar mark made by any cause; a weal; a wale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically <fld>(Med.)</fld>, a flat, burning or
itching eminence on the skin, such as is produced by a mosquito bite, or
in urticaria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wheal
<hw>Wheal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cornish <ets>hwel</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A mine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whealworm</ent>⟦br⟧
